    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground coriander </strong>and <strong>ground cumin </strong>in a bowl with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong> – this is your <strong>BBQ</strong> <strong>spice mix</strong></p><p>Once the meat-free chick'n has warmed through, add the <strong>BBQ spice mix</strong> and the <strong>grated garlic</strong> (not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) to the pan and cook out for 2-3 min or until fragrant – this is your <strong>sweet 'n' smoky BBQ meat-free chick'n fajita filling</strong></p>",
